The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 07 February is 37,758 (4,370.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 02 February, there were 1,795 new confirmed cases (207.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 26 January, there were 2,528 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 29% (733 fewer cases).
